y of HI clouds falling towards the\nGalactic disk and show that most of these must break down into smaller\nfragments that become partially ionized. The Galactic halo is expected to have\nhuge numbers of smaller neutral and ionized fragments. When the ionized\ncomponent is accounted for, the rate of gas accretion is ~0.4 Msun/yr, roughly\ntwice the rate deduced from HI observations alone.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 15 Nov 2008 08:03:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 28 Jan 2009 03:35:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
